#Chapter 1


Append:

i insert text 
I inesrt beginning of line
A append after the line
a append after cursor

#Chapter 2

dw delete from cursor to next word
d$ detete from cursor to end of line
dd delete whole line

to repeat a motion, append with number

format for change command:
operator [number] motion
ie d2$
delete 2 till end of lin

0 to move to start of line

u undo
U undo all changes on a line
CTRL-R redo


#Chapter 3
p put back deleted text
r replace character under cursor
c change from cursor
c [number] motion
c2e
change from cursor to end of second word

#Chapter 4
CTRL-G displays location
G moves to end of file
number G moves to that file number
GG moves to the first line


/ then phrse searches forward
? then phrase searches backward
after search hit n for next
or hit N for previous

CTRL-O takes you to older positions
CTRL-I takes you to newer positions

% takes you to the bracket match

To substitute new for the first old in a line type    :s/old/new               
To substitute new for all 'old's on a line type       :s/old/new/g             
To substitute phrases between two line #'s type       :#,#s/old/new/g          
To substitute all occurrences in the file type        :%s/old/new/g            
To ask for confirmation each time add 'c'             :%s/old/new/gc 



